!Configuring WSJT-X

I configured WSJT-X for QMX+ and all seems correct, but transmit throws an error.

```
Hamlib error: Invalid parameter
ic10_set_mode: unsupported mode PKTUSB
rig_set_mode: targetable retcode after set_mode=-1
rig.c(2048):rig_set_mode return(-1) Invalid parameter
ic10_set_mode: unsupported mode PKTUSB
rig_set_mode: targetable retcode after set_mode=-1
rig_set_mode: targetable retcode after set_mode=-1 while setting current VFO mode
```

I fed this info to google's AI thingy.
It told me my USB cable needed a choke (wrong!) and something else, equally unhelpful.

In the end when I switched from Kenwood TS-440S to Kenwood TS-480, things started to work, although I haven't made a contact yet.  
It goes through the motions, and I can see it thinks it's transmitting.

260519 - bumped max PA to 9V (1.8W) and was able to make contact on 20m at ~800 miles/

