!TXCO Frequency
See manual, p. 69.

I set up WSJT-X to report WSPR calls, and then went to [[Han's website to see the errors|https://qrp-labs.com/images/wsprnet/rxerror.html]] in my clock.

```
Website is reporting -32 (Err)
Dial Frequency: 14,095,600 + 1500 offset = 14,097,100 (XMIT)
Err * 25MHZ/XMIT = (-32) * 1.77 = -56.7 ~= -57
```
While I was typing all that up, my reported error dropped to -5 ==> change TCXO setting by -9.
After change, letting it run for a while, my Err = -10. 
Looks like I changed the wrong direction.  
Try again.

Score!
25,000,009 gets me Err = 0.